"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348915","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-06-15","<p>My Department is working to prepare the legislation necessary to create the new legal status of guardian of the property and affairs of a missing person. We are grateful for the continued assistance in this work of the charity, Missing People, and its pro bono lawyers, Clifford Chance. We will bring forward legislation when Parliamentary time allows.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2015-06-15T15:08:27.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348915/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348915/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348915/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-06-08","Missing Persons: Guardianship","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, when his Department will publish the legislation proposed in its response to its consultation on the Guardianship of the property and affairs of missing persons, published on 23 March 2015.","false","Biography information for Julian Sturdy","York Outer","Julian Sturdy","1400"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348916","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-11","<p /> <p>The Department for Business, Innovation and Skills will deliver £450 million of the Chancellor’s announced £4.5 billion savings announced on the 4th June. The majority of this will be delivered through known underspends and releasing unallocated funding.</p><p> </p><p>Officials in the department are working with the appropriate funding bodies to determine how savings can best be achieved in line with Ministerial priorities.</p><p> </p><p>Priority areas for growth and productivity, including funding for apprenticeships and science, will not be affected – raising the skill level of the workforce and developing new ideas are fundamental drivers of long-run productivity growth.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-06-11T11:45:56.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348916/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348916/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348916/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-08","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Cost Effectiveness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, with reference to HM Treasury's press release, Chancellor announces £4.5 billion of measures to bring down debt, published on 4 June 2015, what assessment he has made of the effect on productivity of delivering efficiency savings from his Department's budget.","false","Biography information for Shabana Mahmood","Birmingham, Ladywood","Shabana Mahmood","1375"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348917","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-15","<p>The majority of the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills’ £450m savings will be delivered through known underspends and releasing unallocated funding.</p><p> </p><p>Officials in my Department are working with the appropriate funding bodies to determine how other savings can best be achieved in line with ministers’ priorities.</p><p> </p><p>Funding for apprenticeships and student maintenance will not be affected.</p><p> </p><p>The underlying principles ensuring that students and young people continue to benefit from one of the best education systems in the world will continue.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-06-15T09:16:52.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348917/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348917/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348917/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-08","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Cost Effectiveness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, with reference to HM Treasury's press release, Chancellor announces £4.5 billion of measures to bring down debt, published on 4 June 2015, what efficiency savings he plans to make to meet the planned reduction of £450 million in his Department's budget; and how much he plans to reduce higher education and further education spending in order to make that reduction.","false","Biography information for Shabana Mahmood","Birmingham, Ladywood","Shabana Mahmood","1376"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348918","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-16","<p>No specific assessment has been made of the effect of the announced measures on productivity. The Department will continue to deliver efficiency savings wherever possible as part of the Government’s Long Term Economic Plan.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-06-16T12:04:41.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348918/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348918/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348918/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-08","Treasury: Cost Effectiveness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to HM Treasury's press release, Chancellor announces £4.5 billion of measures to bring down debt, published on 4 June 2015, what assessment he has made of the effect on productivity of steps necessary to deliver efficiency savings from his Department's budget.","false","Biography information for Shabana Mahmood","Birmingham, Ladywood","Shabana Mahmood","1351"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348919","Department for Education","false","2015-06-15","<p>These savings will come from a variety of measures including expected departmental underspends in demand-led budgets, efficiencies and some small budgetary reductions. No savings will be made from protected schools funding.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2015-06-15T14:05:49.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348919/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348919/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348919/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-06-08","Department for Education: Cost Effectiveness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to the HM Treasury press release, Chancellor announces £4.5 billion of measures to bring down debt, published on 4 June 2015, what efficiency savings she plans to make to meet planned reductions of £450 million in her Department's budget.","false","Biography information for Shabana Mahmood","Birmingham, Ladywood","Shabana Mahmood","1430"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348920","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-15","<p>Officials have held discussions under the aegis of the Cabinet Office-led Telecommunications and Digital Infrastructure Portfolio Board (TDIP) on the potential exploitation of any spare telecoms capacity to benefit the public. No decisions for any changes have been taken and there are no current plans to sell Network Rail’s telecoms or power supply assets.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Derbyshire Dales","Mr Patrick McLoughlin",,"2015-06-15T14:19:06.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348920/answer","Biography information for Sir Patrick McLoughlin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348920/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348920/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-08","Network Rail","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions he has had on the sale of the (a) telecoms and (b) power supply functions of Network Rail; and what plans he has to sell those functions.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","1329"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348921","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-16","<p>We are extremely concerned that Raif Badawi’s sentence has been upheld by the Supreme Court in Saudi Arabia. However we understand that this case is under active consideration in the Saudi Supreme Court and we will continue to watch it closely. We have raised this case at the most senior levels bilaterally with the Saudi Arabian government and our officials in Riyadh have discussed it frequently with European, Canadian, Australian, New Zealand and US Embassies in Riyadh, including earlier last week.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2015-06-16T13:35:08.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348921/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348921/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348921/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-08","Raif Badawi","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with his international counterparts on the punishment of Raif Badawi.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","1378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348922","Department of Health","false","2015-06-16","<p>The Government has mandated Health Education England (HEE) to provide national leadership on education, training and workforce development.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HEE sets out its commissioning intentions based upon the needs of local employers, providers, commissioners and other stakeholders who come together as members of HEE’s Local Education Training Boards (LETBs).</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HEE’s national workforce plan for England is an aggregate of local LETB’s plans, but the advice and input of clinical advisors and patient representatives, as well as the Royal Colleges and other stakeholders, is also listened to and considered. It is this discussion and involvement locally and nationally that makes this a plan for the whole of the National Health Service in England.</p><p> </p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2015-06-16T16:10:21.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348922/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348922/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348922/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-08","NHS: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to ensure that there are adequate staffing levels in mental health and community care.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","1403"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348923","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-16","<p>Creating a Northern Powerhouse enables the North to reach its full potential as a driving force in the UK economy. Investing in science and technology, transport, digital and innovation, culture and tourism across the region – in cities, towns and counties – alongside devolving power, will give the North a powerful new voice.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton","1405","2015-06-16T16:00:34.513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348923/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348923/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348923/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-08","Regional Planning and Development: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps he plans to take to ensure that economic benefits accruing from the Northern Powerhouse policy are felt in every town and city in the region.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","1404"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348924","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-16","<p>Creating a Northern Powerhouse enables the North to reach its full potential as a driving force in the UK economy. Investing in science and technology, transport, digital and innovation, culture and tourism across the region – in cities, towns and counties – alongside devolving power, will give the North a powerful new voice.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton","1404","2015-06-16T16:00:34.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348924/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348924/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348924/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-08","Regional Planning and Development: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps he is taking to ensure that (a) Huddersfield and (b) other smaller towns and cities benefit from policies introduced as part of the Northern Powerhouse policy.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","1405"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348925","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-15","<p>The Government recognises that every city, town and county are key to economic growth. As part of the Northern Powerhouse, the Government is providing the investment and environment to allow local people to benefit fully from that growth.</p><p> </p><p>Huddersfield, and other towns and cities across West Yorkshire and Leeds City Region, will soon start to see significant benefits from the £627 million Growth Deal. This includes the Process Manufacturing Centre at Kirklees College in Huddersfield which will start on site this month, and the Incubation and Innovation Centre at the University of Huddersfield which is due to commence next year.</p><p> </p><p>Across Yorkshire, the Government is investing in transport improvements, as outlined in the Northern Transport Strategy and through Growth Deals for Sheffield City Region (£328 million), York, North Yorkshire and East Riding (£122.2 million) and the Humber (£113.6 million).</p><p> </p><p>In March 2015, a devolution deal was agreed with West Yorkshire and Leeds City Region. This will give council leaders and businesses greater influence over investment decisions on skills, transport, housing and support for small businesses.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2015-06-15T16:03:01.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348925/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348925/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348925/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-08","Regional Planning and Development: Yorkshire and the Humber","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what provisions under the Northern Powerhouse policy will increase (a) economic growth and (b) employment in (i) Huddersfield and (ii) Yorkshire.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","1406"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348926","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-15","<p>The Department is in regular contact with local authorities, businesses, Local Enterprise Partnerships, universities and other stakeholders from across the North regarding the Northern Powerhouse.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2015-06-15T16:05:39.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348926/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348926/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348926/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-08","Regional Planning and Development: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what representations he has received of the potential effect of the Northern Powerhouse policy on smaller towns and cities in the North.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","1407"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348927","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-18","<p>Unemployment in Huddersfield is at its lowest since 2008. In February the Chancellor laid out his Long-term Economic Plan for Yorkshire and Northern Lincolnshire – a crucial step in building the Northern Powerhouse. The plan aims to raise the employment rate of Yorkshire and Northern Lincolnshire so that over 100,000 more people are in employment there during this Parliament. This will be achieved by backing business start-ups and business growth and investment, through projects like the new, Growth-Deal funded, Incubation and Innovation Centre at Huddersfield University which will support jobs growth in the advanced manufacturing and digital and creative sectors.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-06-18T11:45:29.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348927/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348927/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348927/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-08","Employment: Huddersfield","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what plans he has to increase employment in Huddersfield.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","1408"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348928","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-16","<p>We have raised Raif Badawi’s case at the most senior levels in the Government of Saudi Arabia, most recently our Ambassador in Riyadh raised this on 9 June. The Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond), discussed this case in February and in March with the Saudi Minister of the Interior, His Royal Highness Prince Mohammed bin Naif, now the Crown Prince of Saudi Arabia. We understand the case is still under consideration in the Saudi Supreme Court and will continue to watch this case closely.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2015-06-16T13:36:56.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348928/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348928/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348928/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-08","Raif Badawi","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent conversations he has had with the government of Saudi Arabia on the punishment of Raif Badawi.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","1409"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348929","Department of Health","false","2015-06-12","<p><em>Culture Change in the NHS<strong>[1]</strong>,</em> published in February 2015, outlined progress in implementing Sir Robert Francis QC’s Inquiry recommendations. An annexe to this report outlined progress for each of the 290 recommendations[2]. This report shows that for the overwhelming majority of recommendations, progress has either been substantial, or the relevant action is now complete.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Key achievements include new rigorous inspection regime, a robust special measures regime to help struggling hospitals get back on their feet, new Fundamental Standards and a Duty of Candour.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government remains committed to driving change in the key Francis-related areas of leadership, patient safety and the importance of establishing a learning culture in the National Health Service.</p><p> </p><br /><p>[1] <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/403010/culture-change-nhs.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/403010/culture-change-nhs.pdf</a></p><p>[2] <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/403012/culture-change-nhs-annex.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/403012/culture-change-nhs-annex.pdf</a></p><p> </p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2015-06-12T10:54:49.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348929/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348929/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348929/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-08","Mid Staffordshire NHS Foundation Trust Public Inquiry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, which recommendations from the Francis Inquiry (a) his Department implemented during the previous Parliament and (b) he plans to implement during the current Parliament.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","1485"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348930","Scotland Office","false","2015-06-15","<p>The Government has established the Joint Ministerial Working Group on Welfare with the Scottish Government to ensure a smooth transfer of welfare powers.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2015-06-15T11:21:22.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348930/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348930/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348930/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2015-06-08","Social Security Benefits: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what steps the Government is taking to ensure that the transfer of further welfare powers to Scotland is accompanied by clear communication and information sharing between the UK and Scottish Governments.","false","Biography information for Christina Rees","Neath","Christina Rees","1333"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348931","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-11","<p>The Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills will work closely with industry and businesses to understand their needs and what more the Government can do to retain the UK’s competitive position within the global economy. The biggest challenge facing the economy is improving productivity and it is important to recognise that the productivity challenge is different sector by sector. Regular dialogue and working with business, including through the sector councils, as part of our wider industrial approach, is a vital part of that.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","1474 ; 1475","2015-06-11T14:49:58.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348931/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348931/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348931/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-08","Construction Industry Council","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what his policy is on future government support for the Construction Industry Council.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","1473"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348932","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-11","<p>The Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills will work closely with industry and businesses to understand their needs and what more the Government can do to retain the UK’s competitive position within the global economy. The biggest challenge facing the economy is improving productivity and it is important to recognise that the productivity challenge is different sector by sector. Regular dialogue and working with business, including through the sector councils, as part of our wider industrial approach, is a vital part of that.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","1473 ; 1475","2015-06-11T14:49:59.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348932/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348932/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348932/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-08","Automotive Council","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what his policy is on future government support for the Automotive Council.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","1474"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348933","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-11","<p>The Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills will work closely with industry and businesses to understand their needs and what more the Government can do to retain the UK’s competitive position within the global economy. The biggest challenge facing the economy is improving productivity and it is important to recognise that the productivity challenge is different sector by sector. Regular dialogue and working with business, including through the sector councils, as part of our wider industrial approach, is a vital part of that.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","1473 ; 1474","2015-06-11T14:49:59.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348933/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348933/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348933/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-08","Aerospace Growth Partnership","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what his policy is on future government support for the Aerospace Growth Partnership.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","1475"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348934","Department of Health","false","2015-06-16","<p>The Joint Committee on Vaccination and Immunisation (JCVI) Pneumococcal Sub-committee has been undertaking a review of adult pneumococcal vaccination during 2015. Subject to the availability of the necessary data, it is anticipated that the advice of the Pneumococcal Sub-committee will be considered by the JCVI at their next meeting in October 2015.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>As set out in the JCVI Code of Practice, JCVI will consider the advice of the Sub-committee and may decide to issue an interim statement for a short period of consultation with those stakeholders who submitted evidence that informed the Committee’s advice.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The JCVI Code of Practice is available at:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/224864/JCVI_Code_of_Practice_revision_2013_-_final.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/224864/JCVI_Code_of_Practice_revision_2013_-_final.pdf</a></p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-06-16T14:32:59.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348934/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348934/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348934/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-08","Pneumococcal Diseases: Vaccination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when he expects a final decision to be made following completion of the Joint Committee on Vaccination and Immunisation Pneumococcal Sub-committee's review of the adult pneumococcal vaccination programme for (a) over-65s and (b) at-risk groups; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir George Howarth","Knowsley","Mr George Howarth","1489"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348935","Department of Health","false","2015-06-16","<p>As set out in the Joint Committee on Vaccination and Immunisation (JCVI) Code of Practice, the JCVI will consider the advice of the Sub-committee and may decide to issue an interim statement for a short period of consultation with those stakeholders who submitted evidence that informed the Committee’s advice.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The JCVI Code of Practice is available at:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/224864/JCVI_Code_of_Practice_revision_2013_-_final.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/224864/JCVI_Code_of_Practice_revision_2013_-_final.pdf</a></p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-06-16T15:24:51.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348935/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348935/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348935/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-08","Pneumococcal Diseases: Vaccination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether the Joint Committee on Vaccination and Immunisation plans to publish a consultation following the conclusion of the Pneumococcal Sub-committee's review of the adult pneumococcal vaccination programme; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir George Howarth","Knowsley","Mr George Howarth","1490"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348936","Department of Health","false","2015-06-16","<p>The Prime Minister’s Challenge on Dementia 2020 aims that every person with a diagnosis of dementia, their family and their carer should have access to the advice and information on the care and support available to them locally and how this can be accessed.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Challenge would like to see, by 2020, more carers of people with dementia being made aware of and offered the opportunity for respite, education, training, emotional and psychological support so that they feel able to cope with their caring responsibilities and to have a life alongside caring. The Challenge would also like to see more employers having carer friendly policies and practice enabling more carers to continue working and caring.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Department contributed to the funding of the Alzheimer’s Society’s ‘Dementia Guide’, designed to help guide people with dementia and their carers through their journey with dementia. The Guide provides useful information for carers, following a diagnosis of dementia, and includes advice to help people understand a diagnosis of dementia to enable them to live well with the condition.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>There are various resources supported by the Department and NHS England that can be accessed by families and carers. For example the Dementia Roadmap (a web based platform developed by the Royal College of Practitioners) provides high quality information about the dementia journey alongside local information about services, support groups and care pathways, primarily to assist primary care staff to more effectively support people with dementia, their families and carers.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>NHS England’s 2015/16 Dementia Enhanced Service encourages general practitioner practices to increase the health and wellbeing support offered to carers of patients diagnosed with dementia.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Department is supporting the Dementia Action Alliance’s Carers Call to Action and the establishment of a new involvement network for family carers of people with dementia.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Under the Care Act 2014, local authorities have a responsibility to assess carer’s eligible needs for support. This will mean more carers, including carers of people with dementia, are able to have an assessment, comparable to the right of the people they care for, and a support plan setting out how their needs will be met.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-06-16T15:08:09.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348936/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348936/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348936/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-08","Dementia: Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what support and guidance is available from his Department and NHS England for families and carers of people with dementia.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","1491"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348937","Women and Equalities","false","2015-06-16","<p>The Government’s contribution to the five-year review of the Equality Act 2010 is a substantive memorandum intended to facilitate post-legislative scrutiny of the Act, which we aim to publish as a Command paper shortly.</p><p>The memorandum will provide Parliament with a factual account of developments since the Act received Royal Assent five years ago. This will include a summary of why the Act was introduced, a breakdown of which elements have or have not come into force, a list of associated secondary legislation, a summary of key case law and a preliminary assessment outlining whether the Act is achieving its stated aims. Parliament will consider this information before deciding whether to gather further evidence on how the Act is operating.</p><p>Further details of the Government’s approach to post-legislative scrutiny is available in the Cabinet Office’s Guide to Making Legislation at <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/guide-to-making-legislation" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/guide-to-making-legislation</a></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2015-06-16T15:32:18.91Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348937/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348937/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348937/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2015-06-08","Equality Act 2010","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, with reference to the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State's contribution of 18 March 2015, Official Report, Column 310 WH, when the five-year review of the Equality Act 2010 will begin; what the terms of reference of that review will be; whether a public consultation will be held as part of that review; and when that review is expected to report.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","1443"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348938","Cabinet Office","false","2015-06-16","<p>Information on the projected savings can be found at: <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/documents/impact-assessments/IA12-017.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/documents/impact-assessments/IA12-017.pdf</a></p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2015-06-16T15:01:30.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348938/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348938/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348938/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-06-08","Constituencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the Answer of 3 June 2015 to Question 262, how his Department's estimate that reducing the number of Parliamentary constituencies from 650 to 600 would result in savings to the public purse of £13.6 million a year has been calculated.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","1444"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348939","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-06-16","<p>We will consider the implications of a Bill of Rights on devolution as we develop our proposals. However, we have made it clear that we will, of course, fully engage with the devolved administrations.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2015-06-16T15:56:07.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348939/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348939/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348939/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-06-08","Human Rights Act 1998","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 3 June 2015 to Question 368, what discussions he has had with the (a) Scottish Executive, (b) Welsh Executive and (c) Northern Ireland Executive on the Government's plan to repeal the Human Rights Act 1998.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","1445"
