"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349011","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-16","<p>The information requested is not available.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In the March 2015 Budget the Government announced that it would undertake a review of how deeds of variation are used for tax purposes. The findings from this review will be reported in the Autumn.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-06-16T15:54:13.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349011/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349011/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349011/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-08","Inheritance Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will make an estimate of the amount of inheritance tax that has been avoided by the use of Deed of Variations in the tax year (a) 2013-14 and (b) 2014-15.","false","Biography information for John Stevenson","Carlisle","John Stevenson","1402"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349012","Department of Health","false","2015-06-15","<p>This is a matter for the National Health Service locally.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>I have written to David Eva, Chair of Cheshire and Wirral Partnership NHS Foundation Trust, informing him of the hon. Member’s enquiry. He will reply shortly and a copy of the letter will be placed in the Library.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-06-15T12:08:15.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349012/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349012/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349012/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-08","Eating Disorders: Wirral South","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will make an estimate of the cost to Wirral University Teaching Hospital NHS Foundation Trust of specialised eating disorder clinics occurring in Wirral South constituency.","false","Biography information for Alison McGovern","Wirral South","Alison McGovern","1423"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349013","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-06-16","<p /> <p>We have taken translators as Face to Face interpreters, Written Translators and Telephone Interpreters. Please see below the costs breakdown by service provided and total cost that HMCTS have spent on the Capita-TI contract for the last three years:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p><strong> </strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong> </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012-2013</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013-2014</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014-2015</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>FTF</p></td><td><p>£12,075,110</p></td><td><p>£16,040,076</p></td><td><p>£17,214,294</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Translation</p></td><td><p>£42,723</p></td><td><p>£27,196</p></td><td><p>£34,824</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>ITI</p></td><td><p>£14,904</p></td><td><p>£17,140</p></td><td><p>£12,581</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total</p></td><td><p><strong>£12,132,737</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£16,084,412</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£17,261,699</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Before 2012, courts arranged interpreter contracts on an individual basis. The Government has taken steps to ensure the system provides value for taxpayers by agreeing a national contract. Demand for these services has grown as awareness increases amongst court and tribunal users. Since we introduced a new interpreting contract in 2012 we have spent £38.2m less on language service fees.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-06-16T16:55:40.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349013/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349013/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349013/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-06-08","HM Courts and Tribunals Service: Translation Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much HM Courts and Tribunal Service has spent on translators in each of the last three years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for David T. C. Davies","Monmouth","David T. C. Davies","1429"
