"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349019","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-11","<p>As part of its plans for High Speed 2, HS2 Ltd is reviewing its proposals for the redevelopment of Euston Station and is proposing to deposit revised plans for the station in an Additional Provision to the Phase One hybrid Bill later this year.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-06-11T14:27:41.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349019/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349019/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349019/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-08","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when the plans for Euston Station and High Speed 2 will be announced; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","1440"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349020","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-11","<p /> <p>No assessment has been made at the 20<sup>th</sup> percentile.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-11T13:05:16.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349020/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349020/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349020/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-08","Local Housing Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made  of the effect of setting local housing allowance rates at the 20th percentile of market rents on (a) levels of arrears in the private rented sector, (b) viability in the buy-to-let sector and (c) affordability for working families with children.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","1415"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349021","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-11","<p>The Government is considering the responses to the consultation on the route from the West Midlands to Manchester, Leeds and beyond. It will set out how it plans to take forward HS2 Phase Two later this year.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-06-11T14:16:24.083Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349021/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349021/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349021/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-08","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when the Phase 2 route of High Speed 2 will be announced.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","1416"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349022","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-11","<p>Where access to land has been secured, physical surveys have been made possible on over 80% of the route. ‎In those locations where this has not yet been possible, desk based research (for example, using data sets provided from Statutory Agencies, Local Authorities and local Wildlife Trusts) and aerial surveys have been undertaken. The results of these are detailed in the Environmental Statement for Phase One, published to accompany the deposit of the hybrid Bill and the subsequent Additional Provisions.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-06-11T14:19:35.92Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349022/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349022/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349022/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-08","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what proportion of the route of Phase 1 of High Speed 2 has been surveyed.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","1417"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349023","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-11","<p>Advice prepared by HS2 Ltd in conjunction with the Department for Transport, Transport Scotland and the Scotland Office to identify broad options for high speed and upgraded railways to the north of England and Scotland is currently with Ministers for consideration. This advice will be published in due course.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-06-11T14:23:29.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349023/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349023/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349023/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-08","High Speed 2 Railway Line: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when the report on the extension of High Speed 2 to Scotland will be published; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","1418"
