"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348722","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-10","<p /> <p>The Information requested is not available for Personal Independence Payment.</p><p> </p><p>For Employment Support Allowance the average cost of processing</p><p> </p><p>a Mandatory Reconsideration is: £108</p><p> </p><p>an appeal to the Department for Work and Pensions is: £135</p><p> </p><p>The average cost of processing an appeal to the Tribunals Service is £214.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","1298","2015-06-10T16:26:52.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348722/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348722/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348722/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-05","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the average cost is of (a) a reconsideration of and (b) an appeal against a decision on a personal independence payment.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","1297"
