"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348565","Prime Minister","false","2015-06-09","<p>I have nothing further to add.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2015-06-09T15:58:56.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348565/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348565/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348565/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-06-04","Iraq Committee of Inquiry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, pursuant to the Answer of 4 June 2015 to Question 556 on the Chilcot inquiry, whether he has received any information or updates (a) regarding the inquiry since his statements at Prime Minister's Questions on 21 January 2015 and (b) on the work the inquiry has conducted since February 2015.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","1272"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348566","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-09","<p /> <p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 03 June 2015 to Question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-05-27/170/" target="_blank">UIN 170</a></p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-06-09T13:21:41.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348566/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348566/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348566/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-04","Social Security Benefits: Disqualification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will commission an independent review of the sanctions regime.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","1241"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348567","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-09","<p /> <p>No such estimate has been made.</p><p> </p><p>However, in discussing the content of a Claimant Commitment, Jobcentre Plus Work Coaches take into account individual circumstances when agreeing those jobsearch activities that, if undertaken, will offer the claimant best prospects of employment.</p><p> </p><p>Where this includes looking and applying for jobs on-line and the claimant does not have their own Internet access, the Work Coach will agree a reasonable level of activity, taking into account the availability of alternative means of access, e.g. free public access services and Jobcentre Plus computers.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-06-09T13:34:53.993Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348567/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348567/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348567/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-04","Employment: Electronic Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the number of jobseekers required to spend a certain number of hours per week on the Government's online jobs website who are unable to afford their own computer or internet connection.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","1242"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348568","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-09","<p /> <p>Jobseeker’s Allowance claimants with children and anyone categorised as vulnerable, including all Employment Support Allowance claimants, are able to apply for hardship payments from day one of the sanction. The majority of claims are accepted.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>In addition to this, Local Authorities provide assistance to the most vulnerable people in their communities through local welfare provision, which has received an additional £74 million on top of the £129 million previously allocated funding.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-06-09T14:06:21.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348568/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348568/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348568/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-04","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of difficulties caused by the two week waiting period for a hardship payment.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","1243"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348569","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-09","<p /> <p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 03 June 2015 to Question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-05-27/176/" target="_blank">UIN 176</a></p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-06-09T13:26:31.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348569/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348569/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348569/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-04","Social Security Benefits: Disqualification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what his Department's policy is on sanctioning (a) families with children and (b) people suffering from mental health problems.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","1244"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348570","Department for International Development","false","2015-06-09","<p>The UK Government supports the work of various international organisations and agencies to promote informed choice, universal access to sexual and reproductive health and rights and women’s empowerment. All UK support to improve sexual and reproductive health – including for family planning – must be provided in the context of informed choice.</p>","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps",,"2015-06-09T15:40:47.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348570/answer","Biography information for Grant Shapps","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348570/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348570/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-06-04","Developing Countries: Family Planning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps her Department takes to ensure that UK aid is not provided to coercive family-planning schemes or to organisations that are complicit in such schemes.","false","Biography information for Robert Flello","Stoke-on-Trent South","Robert Flello","1151"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348571","Department for International Development","false","2015-06-09","<p>No organisations the UK funds, who work in China, promote the one-child policy. The UK Government supports the work of various international organisations and agencies to promote informed choice, universal access to sexual and reproductive health and rights and women’s empowerment, including voluntary family planning.</p>","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps",,"2015-06-09T15:41:27.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348571/answer","Biography information for Grant Shapps","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348571/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348571/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-06-04","China: Family Planning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, pursuant to the Answer of 1 June 2015 to Question 20, whether any UK funding is provided to multinational organisations that assist organisations that are closely involved with China's one-child policy.","false","Biography information for Robert Flello","Stoke-on-Trent South","Robert Flello","1152"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348572","Department for International Development","false","2015-06-09","<p>The World Health Organisation document “Preventing gender-biased sex selection. An interagency statement”, available online, includes more information and extensive references on these issues.</p>","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps",,"2015-06-09T16:35:16.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348572/answer","Biography information for Grant Shapps","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348572/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348572/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-06-04","Abortion: Gender Selection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, pursuant to the Answer of 1 June 2015 to Question 20, what the evidential basis is for the statement that sex selection is not caused by the availability of abortion services or technologies; whether her Department considers that antenatal scanning equipment facilitates sex-selective abortion; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Robert Flello","Stoke-on-Trent South","Robert Flello","1255"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348573","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-06-23","<p>Superfast broadband coverage is available to over 80% of UK premises and the Government remains committed to providing 95% coverage to homes and businesses by December 2017.</p><p> </p><p>Commercial broadband delivery is expected to cover 13,862 premises in the North Devon constituency. By the end of the Connecting Devon and Somerset project, coverage is expected to have increased to 39,744 premises.</p><p> </p><p>This data is included in the table in the House of Commons Library: <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/business-papers/commons/deposited-papers/?house=1&amp;search_term=Department+for+Culture%2c+Media+and+Sport&amp;itemId=122028#toggle-163" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/business-papers/commons/deposited-papers/?house=1&amp;search_term=Department+for+Culture%2c+Media+and+Sport&amp;itemId=122028#toggle-163</a></p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-06-23T15:47:11.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348573/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348573/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348573/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-04","Broadband: North Devon","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps he plans to take in further extending the availability of superfast broadband in North Devon constituency.","false","Biography information for Peter Heaton-Jones","North Devon","Peter Heaton-Jones","1157"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348574","Department for International Development","false","2015-06-10","<p>We use private contractors to deliver aid where they can provide the best results and value for taxpayers' money, which is the sensible approach to take. In the past year alone, this has included building treatment centres to defeat Ebola in Sierra Leone, delivering life-saving aid to Syrian refugees, and providing shelter to people who have lost their homes in the Nepal earthquake. A recent Independent Commission for Aid Impact (ICAI) report noted that the rates paid by DFID were “highly competitive”. Individual companies set the rates for their contractors.</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2015-06-10T16:01:34.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348574/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348574/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348574/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-06-04","Consultants: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what the maximum daily rate of pay is for consultants (a) directly employed by and (b) employed by contractors working for her Department.","false","Biography information for Jeremy Lefroy","Stafford","Jeremy Lefroy","1106"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348575","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-11","<p>Statistics on Private Registered Provider dwelling stock in England and in each local authority district are published in the Department’s live table 115, which is available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-dwelling-stock-including-vacants" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-dwelling-stock-including-vacants</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-06-11T14:29:13.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348575/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348575/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348575/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-04","Social Rented Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many registered Housing Association properties there are in each English local authority.","false","Biography information for Jeremy Lefroy","Stafford","Jeremy Lefroy","1107"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348576","Department for International Development","false","2015-06-10","<p>Details of individual contractor payments would require extensive research at a disproportionate cost to the UK taxpayer.</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2015-06-10T16:01:53.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348576/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348576/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348576/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-06-04","Department for International Development: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many contractors (a) working directly for and (b) on projects funded by her Department were paid more than £400 a day in financial years (i) 2012-13 and (ii) 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Jeremy Lefroy","Stafford","Jeremy Lefroy","1108"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348577","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-06-10","<p>The ‘Speak Up for the Love of’ climate lobby on the 17 June will be a significant opportunity for people’s voices to be heard on the issue of climate change.</p><p>Campaigning matters – as seen through years of campaigning against apartheid, cancelling debt, Make Poverty History, and recent food campaigns, when people come together in the right spirit, change can happen.</p><p>I welcome next week’s climate lobby – MPs will be listening, and stand ready to act. My noble friend Lord Bourne and I will be engaging with civil society and businesses throughout the day to discuss the UK’s priorities for a climate deal in Paris.</p><p>Securing a global climate deal at the United Nations Framework on Climate Change (UNFCCC) conference in Paris this year is vital to give a clear signal to businesses and investors that Governments are committed to delivering a global low carbon economy. I am pleased the G7 prioritised an ambitious climate package at this year’s Summit, including strong language on the need for a deal in Paris, finance and future ambition. On 10 June, I too, will reiterate the significance of an ambitious deal during debate of the Opposition Day motion on climate change at the House of Commons.</p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2015-06-10T08:35:47.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348577/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348577/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348577/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-06-04","Climate Change","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what steps she is taking to engage with the Climate Lobby in Westminster on 17 June 2015.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","1158"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348578","Department for International Development","false","2015-06-11","<p>DFID is committed to ensuring that the specific needs of the most vulnerable and marginalised, including older people, are addressed in everything DFID does. This includes in our country programmes and humanitarian responses, through DFID-supported social protection programmes such as the Senior Citizen’s Grant in Uganda and by committing to making age-disaggregated data is a requirement for humanitarian financing. DFID also funds a number of civil society organisations who support older people, including a significant partnership with HelpAge International. DFID’s disability framework, published in December 2014, highlights the importance of specifically addressing the needs of older people.</p>","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps",,"2015-06-11T12:57:48.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348578/answer","Biography information for Grant Shapps","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348578/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348578/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-06-04","Developing Countries: Older People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps she has taken to ensure that the UK's international development strategy supports older people.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","1159"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348579","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-10","<p /> <p>We have received no such representations. However, the paper industry is an important part of the UK’s manufacturing infrastructure. This Government recognises the challenges facing energy-intensive sectors such as paper, and we have taken steps to reduce the cumulative impact of energy and climate change policies on industrial electricity prices this industry faces. Building on the achievement of a £10 billion saving for business from deregulation in the last Parliament, we have also committed to reducing business red tape by a further £10 billion over the next five years.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-06-10T11:42:52.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348579/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348579/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348579/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-04","Paper","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what representations he has received on the regulatory framework for the UK paper industry.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","1160"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348580","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-12","<p>The Great Western electrification is the biggest and most complex electrification scheme for more than a generation and it is planned to be completed during Control Period 5.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-06-12T11:40:17.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348580/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348580/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348580/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-04","Railways: Swansea","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what progress has been made on electrification of the mainline between London and Swansea; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Christina Rees","Neath","Christina Rees","1268"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348581","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-12","<p>We have committed to capping regulated rail fares at the Retail Price Inflation (RPI) for five years from 2016 and we have also stopped operators increasing individual regulated fares by up to 2% more than RPI. Train operators will use the July 2015 RPI figure, published in August, to set regulated rail fares for 2016. Data on these fares will be published in December 2015.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-06-12T11:26:56.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348581/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348581/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348581/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-04","Railways: Fares","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of average change in regulated rail fares between 2015 and 2016.","false","Biography information for Christina Rees","Neath","Christina Rees","1240"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348582","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-10","<p>Whilst we do not hold any information about how other Member States apply or interpret the provisions in the Habitats Directive in relation to bats in churches, the Government understands the problems that the presence of bats can cause.</p><p>To assist churches, Defra has funded research to identify techniques that can be used to deter bats from sensitive areas of churches, the results of which were published in March 2014. English Heritage is now funding a project trialling the techniques identified by this research in several churches to develop a toolkit and advice pack. A bid for Heritage Lottery funding to help pay for the implementation of this toolkit is also being prepared.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2015-06-10T11:20:24.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348582/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348582/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348582/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-04","Bats: Churches","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what information her Department holds on the application and interpretation of provisions in the Habitats Directive on bats inhabiting church premises in other EU member states.","false","Biography information for Dame Caroline Spelman","Meriden","Mrs Caroline Spelman","1114"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348583","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-09","<p>Highways England (formerly the Highways Agency) is responsible for the Strategic Road Network and Cumbria County Council for the local road network within the Workington constituency and Allerdale district. The A595 Parton to Lillyhall improvement was the one major project that Highways England were responsible for in the wider Allerdale district since 2005. The spend profile since 2005/06 is shown below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2005/06</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2006/07</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2007/08</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2008/09</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2009/10</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2010/11</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Spend (£m)</p></td><td><p>0.95</p></td><td><p>4.785</p></td><td><p>14.616</p></td><td><p>20.534</p></td><td><p>0.596</p></td><td><p>0.539</p></td><td><p><strong>42.642</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Highways England spent the following amounts on maintenance and improvements:</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="2"><p>Allerdale District</p></td><td> </td><td> </td><td colspan="2"><p>Workington Constituency</p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>£ million</p></td><td> </td><td> </td><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>£ million</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2005/2006</p></td><td><p>0.917</p></td><td> </td><td> </td><td><p>2005/2006</p></td><td><p>0.050</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2006/2007</p></td><td><p>2.123</p></td><td> </td><td> </td><td><p>2006/2007</p></td><td><p>0.055</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2007/2008</p></td><td><p>2.536</p></td><td> </td><td> </td><td><p>2007/2008</p></td><td><p>0.004</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2008/2009</p></td><td><p>1.917</p></td><td> </td><td> </td><td><p>2008/2009</p></td><td><p>0.016</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009/2010</p></td><td><p>2.151</p></td><td> </td><td> </td><td><p>2009/2010</p></td><td><p>0.246</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/2011</p></td><td><p>1.365</p></td><td> </td><td> </td><td><p>2010/2011</p></td><td><p>0.210</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/2012</p></td><td><p>0.484</p></td><td> </td><td> </td><td><p>2011/2012</p></td><td><p>0.010</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/2013</p></td><td><p>1.476</p></td><td> </td><td> </td><td><p>2012/2013</p></td><td><p>0.000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/2014</p></td><td><p>2.553</p></td><td> </td><td> </td><td><p>2013/2014</p></td><td><p>0.052</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/2015</p></td><td><p>1.597</p></td><td> </td><td> </td><td><p>2014/2015</p></td><td><p>0.070</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The Department for Transport provides funding to local highway authorities for the local road network. For Cumbria County Council the allocations since 2005 are as follows:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>£ million</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2005/06</p></td><td><p>15.816</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2006/07</p></td><td><p>17.378</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2007/08</p></td><td><p>18.691</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2008/09</p></td><td><p>19.801</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009/10</p></td><td><p>26.478</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>58.27</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>49.197</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>34.772</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>47.616</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>40.666</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>36.708</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>Cumbria have also been allocated £24.6 million through the Local Growth Fund announced in July 2014 and January 2015 for transport schemes including £2m towards replacement of a life expired road bridge that provides access to the Port of Workington.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-06-09T15:43:30.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348583/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348583/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348583/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-04","Roads: Cumbria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what investment in road infrastructure there has been in (a) Workington constituency and (b) Allerdale district in each year since 2005.","false","Biography information for Sue Hayman","Workington","Sue Hayman","1146"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348584","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-09","<p>The Government remains committed to improving bus services for all and expenditure on buses reflects this. It is for individual local authorities to determine how much of the block grant funding they receive is allocated to supporting bus services. The latest out-turn figures, for 2013/14, show that Cumbria County Council has an annual budget of over £2.5m for this purpose.</p><p> </p><p>The Department also provides direct support to bus services each year through Bus Service Operators Grant (BSOG), of which Cumbria County Council has received £480,314 covering the 2014/15 financial year.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-06-09T10:00:12.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348584/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348584/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348584/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-04","Bus Services: Cumbria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to improve the provision of local bus services in Cumbria.","false","Biography information for Sue Hayman","Workington","Sue Hayman","1147"
