"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348618","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-29","<p>The Troubled Families initiative aims to turn families around. This means children are back in school for three consecutive terms and there has been significant reductions in youth crime and anti-social behaviour; or an adult in the family is back in work for at least three months. The first Troubled Families Programme is on track to achieve its goal to turn around the lives of 120,000 troubled families across England by May 2015. As of February 2015, over 105,000 families had been turned around. Final results will be published shortly. <br><br>The first programme has been subject to an independent national evaluation carried out by a consortium of research organisations, led by Ecorys UK Ltd and comprising Ipsos MORI, The National Institute for Economic and Social Research, Bryson Purdon Research and Clarissa White Research. The evaluation is assessing the impact, process and cost benefit of the programme. In July 2014, an initial report on the characteristics and problems experienced by families in the programme was published titled <em>Understanding Troubled Families</em>. The full final evaluation report is due later this summer.</p><p>The new expanded Troubled Families Programme aims to help up to 400,000 additional families achieve significant and sustainable change. It was rolled out nationally in April 2015 and an evaluation of this programme has already begun, delivered by the Office of National Statistics, Ipsos MORI and The Stationary Office. This will build on the first programme's assessments of impact and cost benefit, alongside a programme of qualitative research with local authorities and families to understand if and how services have adapted to work more effectively with families and those families' experiences of services.</p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark","1166 ; 1168","2015-06-29T13:11:56.733Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348618/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348618/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348618/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-04","Families: Disadvantaged","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what plans his Department has for future continuous assessment of the Troubled Families initiative.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","1169"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348619","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-10","<p /> <p>Assessing the impact of the Department’s policies on families is an integral part of policy development in the Department.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-06-10T10:25:36.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348619/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348619/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348619/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-04","Department for Business Innovation and Skills: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, with reference to the Prime Minister's press release of 18 August 2014, what steps he is taking to assess the impact of his Department's policies on the family.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","1187"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348620","Attorney General","false","2015-06-10","<p>The Family Test was announced by the Prime Minister in August 2014 and introduced in October 2014 through the publication of guidance for officials -<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf" target="_blank">Family Test Guidance</a></p><p>The objective of the Test is to introduce a family perspective to the policy making process, specifically to make the potential impacts on family functioning and relationships explicit.</p><p>The Law Officers’ Departments have not applied the Test to date, however where applicable they would work with the DWP to embed the Test in policymaking processes.</p>","South Swindon","Robert Buckland",,"2015-06-10T09:56:21.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348620/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348620/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348620/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2015-06-04","Attorney General: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, with reference to the press release released by the Prime Minister on 18 August 2014, what steps he is taking to assess the impact of the Law Officers' Departments' policies on the family.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","1188"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348621","Cabinet Office","false","2015-06-08","<p>The Family Test was announced by the Prime Minister in August 2014 and introduced in October 2014, through the publication of guidance for officials - which can be found online at: https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf</p><p>The objective of the Test is to introduce a family perspective to the policy making process, specifically to make the potential impacts on family functioning and relationships explicit.</p><p>The Cabinet Office is working with the Department for Work and Pensions, and other government departments, to embed the Test in the policymaking process.</p><p> </p>","West Dorset","Mr Oliver Letwin",,"2015-06-08T14:51:24.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348621/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Letwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348621/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348621/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-06-04","Cabinet Office: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, with reference to the Prime Minister's press release of 18 August 2014, what steps he is taking to assess the impact of his Department's policies on the family.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","1189"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348622","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-15","<p>The Family Test was announced by the Prime Minister in August 2014 and introduced in October 2014 through the publication of guidance for officials - <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf" target="_blank">Family Test Guidance</a></p><p> </p><p>The objective of the Test is to introduce a family perspective to the policy making process, specifically to make the potential impacts on family functioning and relationships explicit.</p><p> </p><p>DCLG leads on delivery of the Troubled Families Programme which is a leading example of this approach and is working with the Department for Work and Pensions to embed the Test across its wider policy-making process.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2015-06-15T14:46:34.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348622/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348622/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348622/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-04","Department for Communities and Local Government: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to the Prime Minister's press release of August 2014, what steps he is taking to assess the impact of his Department's policies on the family.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","1190"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348623","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-06-23","<p>The Family Test was announced by the Prime Minister in August 2014 and introduced in October 2014 through the publication of guidance for officials - <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf" target="_blank">Family Test Guidance</a></p><p> </p><p>The objective of the Test is to introduce a family perspective to the policy making process, specifically to make the potential impacts on family functioning and relationships explicit.</p><p> </p><p>The Department for Culture, Media and Sport has not applied the Test to date. The Department for Culture, Media and Sport is working with the DWP to embed the Test in the policymaking process.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-06-23T15:52:16.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348623/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348623/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348623/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-04","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to the Prime Minister's press release of 18 August 2014, what steps he is taking to assess the impact of his Department's policies on the family.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","1191"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348624","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-09","<p>Armed Forces families are an integral and valued part of the Armed Forces community. We ask a great deal of our Service personnel and, in return, they deserve to have confidence that their families are appropriately supported.</p><p>Over the last five years this Government has achieved significant successes in this area; we amended the schools admissions code to allow schools in England to allocate a place in advance of a Service family arriving in the area, and enabled infant schools in England to admit Service children over the class size of 30. In addition, we allocated £20 million in LIBOR money in Financial Year 2014-15 to support childcare infrastructure for Service families.</p><p>One of the key tools we use to understand how Armed Forces families feel about the policies which affect them is the annual Families Continuous Attitude Survey (FAMCAS) which monitors the views of spouses and civil partners of Service personnel in key welfare areas, including employment, schooling, healthcare and accommodation. The results of the survey are used to help develop and track military personnel policies. In excess of 7,000 people completed the 2014 FAMCAS survey, with the responses showing improvements in areas such as full-time employment rates for spouses which increased from 33% in 2010 to 40% in 2014 and the numbers owning their own home, which increased from 55% to 58% in the same period.</p><p>In addition to the use of FAMCAS, officials work closely with each Service, the Service Families Federations and Armed Forces charities to understand and respond to family issues. At a senior level, the Families Forum meetings and Service Charities Partnership Board meetings provide regular opportunities for family issues to be raised and monitored with Ministers and the Chief of Defence People.</p><p>I recognise that there is more we can do to support families, which is why I am determined to drive forward projects such as the New Employment Model which aims to produce a modernised offer that reduces the impact of Service life on individuals and their families.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-06-09T15:18:28.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348624/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348624/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348624/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-04","Ministry of Defence: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the Prime Minister's press release of 18 August 2014, what steps he is taking to assess the impact of his Department's policies on the family.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","1192"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348625","Department for Education","false","2015-06-10","<p>The Department for Education has developed comprehensive internal guidance on the Family Test and its application. The Department is confident in the approach it has taken to provide guidance and support to staff in applying the Family Test to new policies.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2015-06-10T16:02:46.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348625/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348625/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348625/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-06-04","Department for Education: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to the Prime Minister's press release of 18 August 2014, what steps she is taking to assess the impact of her Department's policies on the family.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","1193"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348626","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-06-10","<p>The Family Test was announced by the Prime Minister in August 2014 and introduced in October 2014 through the publication of guidance for officials:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf</a></p><p>The objective of the Test is to introduce a family perspective to the policy making process, specifically to make the potential impacts on family functioning and relationships explicit.</p><p>DECC has not applied the Test to date. DECC is working with the DWP to embed the Test in the policymaking process.</p><p>DECC does publish analysis of the estimated impacts of energy and climate change polices on household energy bills across different types of households showing that for each different household composition, energy bills are estimated to be lower on average as a result of these policies. [1] We will continue to consider the impacts on families where relevant, for example when implementing the fuel poverty strategy.</p><p><em><strong>[1]</strong></em><em> DECC (2014) ‘Estimated impacts of energy and climate change policies on energy prices and bills’, available online at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/estimated-impacts-of-energy-and-climate-change-policies-on-energy-prices-and-bills-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/estimated-impacts-of-energy-and-climate-change-policies-on-energy-prices-and-bills-2014</a> Analysis refers to 2020.</em></p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-06-10T16:03:39.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348626/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348626/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348626/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-06-04","Department of Energy and Climate Change: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, with reference to Prime Minister's press release of 18 August 2014, what steps she is taking to assess the impact of her Department's policies on the family.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","1194"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348627","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-10","<p>The Family Test was announced by the Prime Minister in August 2014 and introduced in October 2014 through the publication of guidance for officials - Family Test Guidance</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The objective of the test is to introduce a family perspective to the policy making process, specifically to make the potential impacts on family functioning and relationships explicit.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Defra is following guidance issued by the Department of Work and Pensions to embed and implement the test in the policymaking process. Where the test identifies impacts on the family, this will be evidenced as part of the formal Impact Assessment.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-06-10T16:11:36.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348627/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348627/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348627/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-04","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, with reference to the Prime Minister's press release of 18 August 2014, what steps she is taking to assess the impact of her Department's policies on the family.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","1195"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348628","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-11","<p>The Family Test was announced by the Prime Minister in August 2014 and introduced in October 2014 through the publication of guidance for officials - Family Test Guidance.</p><p>The objective of the Test is to introduce a family perspective to the policy making process, specifically to make the potential impacts on family functioning and relationships explicit.</p><p>The Foreign and Commonwealth (FCO) has not applied the Test to date as The Family Test applies to domestic policy only.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2015-06-11T14:53:49.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348628/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348628/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348628/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-04","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, with reference to the Prime Minister's press release of 18 August 2014, what steps he is taking to assess the impact of his Department's policies on the family.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","1196"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348629","Department of Health","false","2015-06-11","<p>The Family Test was announced by the Prime Minister in August 2014 and introduced in October 2014 through the publication of guidance for officials - Family Test Guidance.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The objective of the Test is to introduce a family perspective to the policy making process, specifically to make the potential impacts on family functioning and relationships explicit.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Department is working to raise awareness of the Family Test amongst its policy staff, so that the impact of policy on the family is considered as a matter of course. The Family Test is highlighted in policy induction training, which is available to staff who are new to policy roles in the Department. The Family Test is also highlighted through the PolicyKit, an online resource for the Department’s policy officials.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-06-11T10:26:24.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348629/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348629/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348629/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-04","Department of Health: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, with reference to the Prime Minister's press release of 18 August 2014, what steps he is taking to assess the impact of his Department's policies on the family.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","1197"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348630","Home Office","false","2015-06-09","<p>As part of the policy development process Home Office officials are expected to consider the published Family Test guidance when assessing the impacts of the Department’s policies. The Family Test is actively being considered for a number of Home Office policies currently in development. The guidance can be found here -</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf</a></p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2015-06-09T11:54:22.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348630/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348630/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348630/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-06-04","Home Office: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the Prime Minister's press release of August 2014, what steps she is taking to assess the impact of her Department's policies on the family.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","1198"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348631","Department for International Development","false","2015-06-11","<p>The Family Test was announced by the Prime Minister in August 2014 and introduced in October 2014 for domestic policies through the publication of guidance for officials – Family Test Guidance.</p><p> </p><p>The objective of the Test is to introduce a family perspective to the policy-making process, specifically to make the potential impacts on family functioning and relationships explicit.</p><p> </p><p>The Department for International Development (DFID) leads the UK’s work to end extreme poverty internationally. In this respect the welfare of the world’s poorest – both individuals and families – are central to DFID’s work. DFID does not however have a leading responsibility for domestic policies and has not therefore made any assessments using the Family Test.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps",,"2015-06-11T12:58:39.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348631/answer","Biography information for Grant Shapps","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348631/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348631/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-06-04","Department for International Development: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, with reference to the Prime Minister's press release of 18 August 2014, what steps she is taking to assess the impact of her Department's policies on the family.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","1199"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348632","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-06-11","<p>The Family Test was announced by the Prime Minister in August 2014 and introduced in October 2014 through the publication of guidance for officials - <a title="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf" target="_blank">Family Test Guidance</a></p><p>The Ministry of Justice has applied the Test since it was introduced. The DWP is working with all departments to embed the Test in the policymaking process.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2015-06-11T12:12:48.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348632/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348632/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348632/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-06-04","Ministry of Justice: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, with reference to the Prime Minister's press release of 18 August 2014, what steps he is taking to assess the impact of his Department's policies on the family.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","1200"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348633","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-06-11","<p>The majority of Northern Ireland policy which has an impact on the family is devolved. The Northern Ireland Office will consider any implications for, and impact on, families in its policymaking process.</p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2015-06-11T12:12:37.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348633/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348633/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348633/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-06-04","Northern Ireland Office: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, with reference to the Prime Minister's press release of 18 August 2014, what steps she is taking to assess the impact of her Department's policies on the family.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","1201"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348634","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-12","<p>The Family Test was announced by the Prime Minister in August 2014 and introduced in October 2014 through the publication of guidance for officials - <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf" target="_blank">Family Test Guidance</a></p><p> </p><p>The objective of the Test is to introduce a family perspective to the policy making process, specifically to make the potential impacts on family functioning and relationships explicit.</p><p> </p><p>The Department for Transport’s internal procedures have been updated to reflect this guidance.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-06-12T11:07:32.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348634/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348634/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348634/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-04","Department for Transport: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to the Prime Minister's press release of August 2014, what steps he is taking to assess the impact of his Department's policies on the family.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","1202"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348635","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-09","<p>The Family Test was announced by the Prime Minister in August 2014 and introduced in October 2014 through the publication of guidance for officials - The Family Test - Guidance for Government Departments available at gov.uk.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The objective of the Test is to introduce a family perspective to the policy making process, specifically to make the potential impacts on family functioning and relationships explicit.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Treasury has been working with the DWP to embed the Test in the policymaking process.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-06-09T14:05:00.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348635/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348635/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348635/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-04","Treasury: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to Prime Minister's press release of 18 August 2014, what steps he is taking to assess the impact of his Department's policies on the family.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","1203"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348636","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-10","<p /> <p>The Family Test was announced by the Prime Minister in August 2014 and introduced in October 2014 through the publication of guidance for officials - <strong> </strong><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Family Test Guidance</strong></a></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The objective of the Test is to introduce a family perspective to the policy making process, specifically to make the potential impacts on family functioning and relationships explicit.</p><p> </p><p>DWP has applied the Test to a number of policies and is also working to embed the Test across Government.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-06-10T11:19:31.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348636/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348636/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348636/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-04","Department for Work and Pensions: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to the Prime Minister's press release of 18 August 2014, what steps he is taking to assess the impact of his Department's policies on the family.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","1204"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348637","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-10","<p>No farmers have had to resubmit their Basic Payment Scheme applications. Farmers were asked to notify the Rural Payment Agency of any changes to their land details as part of the application process.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-06-10T13:50:20.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348637/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348637/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348637/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-04","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many UK farmers have had to resubmit their Basic Payment Scheme applications as a result of errors in the information supplied to them on paper based pre-populated forms and maps.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","1230"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348638","Prime Minister","false","2015-06-09","<p>Andrew Dunlop has served in the Prime Minister’s Office policy unit in two Governments, has wide-ranging experience of government, politics and business, played an important part in the Scottish Independence Referendum and is widely respected across the political divide in Scotland.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2015-06-09T15:56:29.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348638/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348638/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348638/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-06-04","Scotland Office: Junior Ministers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, what criteria he used to select Andrew Dunlop for appointment to the post of Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Scotland.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","1264"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348639","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-10","<p>Between April 2011 and March 2015, £134m of partnership funding contributions were provided towards new flood and coastal erosion management schemes. This represents around 5% of the £2.4bn in Defra funding provided for flood schemes over the same period.</p><p /> <p>Around 25% of the £134m originated from private sector sources and the remainder from the public sector.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2015-06-10T09:49:37.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348639/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348639/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348639/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-04","Flood Control","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what proportion of the funding for flood protection was provided through (a) her Department's standard partnership funding framework, (b) private sector contributions and (c) other public sector contributions as at 31 March 2015.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","1231"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348640","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-11","<p>As a result of this Government’s long-term economic plan, the NHS budget increased in real terms over the last Parliament. In this Parliament, the Government will secure the future of the NHS in England by investing in the NHS’s own five-year plan. Decisions on future departmental savings will be taken at the Spending Review later this year.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2015-06-11T15:33:34.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348640/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348640/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348640/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-04","NHS: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of allocating an additional £8 billion to the NHS by 2020 on funding available for other departments.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","1265"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348641","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-09","<p>No farmers have had to resubmit their Basic Payment Scheme applications. The data submitted through the online system has been captured and information entered will assist processing of Basic Payment Scheme claims.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-06-09T09:05:49.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348641/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348641/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348641/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-04","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many UK farmers have had to resubmit their Basic Payment scheme application because of data being lost when submitted through the online system operated by the Rural Payments Agency; and what her policy is on providing compensation to such people.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","1222"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348642","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-06-09","<p>The Digital Infrastructure and Inclusion Implementation Taskforce will meet as and when required, and the Prime Minister will be updated on a regular basis.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-06-09T12:45:52.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348642/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348642/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348642/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-04","Digital Infrastructure and Inclusion Implementation Taskforce","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how often he plans that the Digital Infrastructure and Inclusion Ministerial implementation taskforce he chairs will meet; and how often that body will report to the Prime Minister.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","1223"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348643","Department for International Development","false","2015-06-09","<p>DFID supports the Myanmar Education Consortium (MEC) which has the key objective of increasing the number and proportion of children who complete a quality basic education. MEC works with a range of Non-Governmental Organisations, including faith-based organisations, provided that i) the education services are available to members of different religious communities, ii) the project activities supported by MEC do not aim to proselytize or explicitly promote a particular religion and iii) the organisations do not engage in any action that could promote inter-communal tensions and where possible promote inter-communal peace and conflict resolution.</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2015-06-09T16:40:25.817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348643/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348643/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348643/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-06-04","Burma: Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what funding her Department provides to religious organisations in Burma for education programmes; and what conditions her Department places on such funding.","false","Biography information for Valerie  Vaz","Walsall South","Valerie Vaz","1233"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348644","Department for International Development","false","2015-06-09","<p>The UK Government has not provided any funding directly to the government of Burma in developing the National Education Law. DFID, together with other international development partners (donors, NGOs etc), has funded technical inputs to the Burmese Ministry of Education’s evidence-based review of the education sector. This review has informed the development of the National Education Law.</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2015-06-09T16:40:51.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348644/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348644/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348644/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-06-04","Burma: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assistance her Department has provided to the government of Burma on the drafting of legislative proposals in that country on education reform.","false","Biography information for Valerie  Vaz","Walsall South","Valerie Vaz","1234"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348645","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-10","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 2 June 2015 to Question number 430.</p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-06-10T15:57:17.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348645/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348645/answer","HOC 403  2 June 2015.doc","Hansard Extract Clyde Naval Base Safety","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348645/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-04","Clyde Naval Base","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Written Statement of 28 May 2015 on safety at HM Naval Base Clyde, if he will place in the Library the written report he received on the investigation into each of the claims made by Able Seaman McNeilly.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","1266"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348646","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-19","<p>There is evidence that having a directly-elected mayor improves economic performance. Fragmented decision-making is linked to poor productivity, and most of the world's greatest cities have strong elected mayors who champion their cities internationally, are directly accountable to the whole city and who can take personal responsibility for dealing with issues like transport, economic development or fighting crime.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Since forming a Combined Authority in 2011, the local councils in Manchester have demonstrated that they work well together and carry out their responsibilities to the people of Manchester effectively. As such, when the combined authority made a compelling bid for further devolution of powers to a Mayor of Manchester, the Government was happy to support their proposals. If other combined authorities come forward with similarly strong proposals the Government would be happy to consider these similarly.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2015-06-19T13:15:03.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348646/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348646/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348646/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-04","Mayors: Greater Manchester","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what policy analysis prompted the Government's decision to propose a directly elected mayor in Manchester.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","1267"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348647","Cabinet Office","false","2015-06-09","<p>The Cabinet Office is responsible for the Government Digital Service (GDS) and it falls within my portfolio as Minister for the Cabinet Office.</p><p>GDS design, build and run digital platforms and infrastructure in conjunction with Departments. GDS also work to improve the technology and digital skills of the civil service.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-06-09T14:58:58.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348647/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348647/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348647/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-06-04","Digital Technology","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what his Department's responsibilities are on digital government and wider digital and technology policy; and which Minister in his Department has day-to-day responsibility for those issues.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","1224"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348648","Attorney General","false","2015-06-09","<p>The Serious Fraud Office has been following closely the emerging allegations and holds material which it is actively reviewing.</p><p> </p><p>I meet the Director and other Ministers frequently to discuss a variety of issues. However, as was the case with previous Administrations, it is not the Government’s policy to provide details of all such meetings.</p>","South Swindon","Robert Buckland",,"2015-06-09T10:30:17.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348648/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348648/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348648/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2015-06-04","FIFA: Corruption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, what assessment he has made of the recent report by the US Department of Justice containing indictments against several senior football officials for corruption, bribery and racketeering in the British Overseas Territories of British Virgin Islands, Cayman Islands and the Turks and Caicos Islands; and what discussions he has had with (a) the Secretary of State for Justice and (b) the Serious Fraud Office about potential prosecution of people named in that report.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","1275"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348649","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-12","<p>The Rural Payments Agency does not record the number of customers who call into drop in centres. 375 pre requested appointments have been completed so far and over 500 others are expected to conclude over the coming week. Our 50 drop in centres have provided a range of support to farmers, initially allowing them to register on to Rural Payments helping us register more than 81,000 customers, and receiving completed claims.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-06-12T13:29:33.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348649/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348649/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348649/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-04","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many farmers have been helped at each of the drop-in centres established by the Rural Payments Agency to help register claims under the Basic Payment scheme.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","1183"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348650","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-11","<p>The Rural Payments Agency has said it will be making full payments as early as possible in the payment window. Payments will start from December and the vast majority will be made by the end of January.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-06-11T13:56:48.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348650/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348650/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348650/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-04","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what proportion of Basic Payment scheme payments will be made to UK farmers when the payment window opens in December 2015; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","1184"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348651","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-10","<p>We continue to monitor these cases and provide consular support and advice to the New Zealand Embassy in Rangoon on Mr Blackwood’s case. Our Embassy in Rangoon regularly lobbies the Burmese government on issues of fundamental rights including freedom of expression. While we have not raised these cases bilaterally, there will an opportunity to raise freedom of expression cases during the EU Burma Human Rights Dialogue on 18 June.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2015-06-10T14:14:34.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348651/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348651/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348651/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-04","Burma: Prisoners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make representations to his Burmese counterpart seeking the release of Philip Blackwood, Tun Thurein and Htut Ko Ko Lwin from prison in that country.","false","Biography information for Valerie  Vaz","Walsall South","Valerie Vaz","1235"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348652","Home Office","false","2015-06-09","<p>The Government accepts the Ombudsman's determination in full and recognises that there are other individuals, including retired police officers, who are affected by the principles set out in this determination. The Government is working with pension administrators to identify affected individuals and ensure that the appropriate payments are made as quickly as possible.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-06-09T11:55:31.063Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348652/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348652/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348652/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-06-04","Home Office: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the implications for her Department's policies are of the decision of the Pension Ombudsman in the case of Mr Milne on 15 May 2015; and if she will make a statement on that ruling.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","1238"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348653","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-06-09","<p>The Digital Economy Unit has moved to the Department for Culture Media and Sport to create a strong focus on the Digital Economy within Government. The move builds on the success of the joint Department for Business, Innovation &amp; Skills and Department for Culture Media and Sport unit which has been operating for almost a year. The unit will continue to work closely with the Department for Business and across Whitehall. The Digital Inclusion team within the Cabinet Office continues to lead on digital inclusion - equipping individuals, small and medium-sized enterprises and the voluntary community and social enterprise sector, with the basic digital skills needed to make the most of being online and to motivate them to do so.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-06-09T12:54:02.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348653/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348653/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348653/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-04","Digital Technology","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, why responsibilities for digital economy have been moved to his Department; whether his Department is responsible for digital inclusion; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","1258"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348654","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-09","<p>The information could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-06-09T16:34:32.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348654/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348654/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348654/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-04","Child Benefit","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many two parent families with a combined income above £50,000 claim child benefit.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","1239"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348655","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-09","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by my right hon. Friend, the Secretary of State for Defence (Michael Fallon) to the hon. Member for Stroud (Neil Carmichael) during Defence Questions on 8 June (Official Report, column 889).</p><p>Deployment timelines will depend on coalition needs but expect that the expansion will be complete in around three months.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-06-09T15:35:51.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348655/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348655/answer","20150608_Iraq_ISIL_Oral_Questions[1].doc","20150608 - Hansard extract on Iraq","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348655/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-04","Iraq: Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the increase will be in armed forces personnel deployed to Iraq to train local forces; and when they will be deployed.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","1246"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348656","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-09","<p>Since October 2014 the UK has trained 1,408 Peshmerga and a further 120 are currently undergoing training.</p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-06-09T15:34:26.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348656/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348656/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348656/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-04","Iraq: Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Peshmerga personnel have received training and support from UK forces personnel in Iraq.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","1247"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348657","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-09","<p>The target strength of the Royal Air Force for the next five financial years is as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="5"><p>RAF Target Strength</p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>2016-17</p></td><td><p>2017-18</p></td><td><p>2018-19</p></td><td><p>2019-20</p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>33,519</p></td><td><p>33,492</p></td><td><p>32,502</p></td><td><p>32,855</p></td><td><p>32,013</p><p> </p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-06-09T15:33:55.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348657/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348657/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348657/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-04","Air Force: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the target strength of the Royal Air Force is for each of the next five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","1248"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348658","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-09","<p>Under Army 2020 the size of the Army will be around 82,000. This figure was reaffirmed in the 2015 Conservative manifesto.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-06-09T15:35:07.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348658/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348658/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348658/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-04","Army: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the target strength of the Army is for each of the next five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","1249"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348659","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-09","<p>A map of the land to be sold in the vicinity of Kings Cross station is attached. The £200 million of other savings to be made in 2015-16 are as follows:</p><p> </p><p>£124 million from reduced contingency;</p><p>£31 million reduction in grant to Transport for London;</p><p>£23 million from Cycling Cities Ambition budget;</p><p>£16 million from Regional Air Connectivity fund;</p><p>£5 million from the Stations Commercial Projects Facility;</p><p>£1 million from Sheffield Tram-Train project.</p><p> </p><p>The return of expected 2015-16 underspends on these projects does not mean that they have been cancelled.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-06-09T15:36:51.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348659/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348659/answer","001260 - Kings Cross map.pdf","1260 - Map of Kings Cross","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348659/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-04","Department for Transport: Cost Effectiveness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to the statement by HM Treasury of 4 June 2015, if he will publish a map of the land to be sold in the vicinity of King's Cross station; how he intends to achieve the other £200 million of savings expected from his Department in 2015-16; and from which cost headings such savings will be made.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","1260"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348660","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-09","<p>The current maximum permitted line speed of a bi-modal IEP train in regular service when running on (a) diesel and (b) electric power is 125 miles per hour.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-06-09T09:48:22.533Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348660/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348660/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348660/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-04","Rolling Stock: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 2 June 2015 to Question 395, what the maximum permitted line speed of the bi-modal IEP train in regular service will be when that train is running on (a) diesel and (b) electric power.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","1261"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348661","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-09","<p>The £500 million savings and adjustments announced will be found from areas such as reducing running costs including expenditure on consultants, overtime and travel, and re-profiling some equipment and infrastructure spend. The agreement does not impact on manpower numbers, current operations, or the increase in equipment spend to which we are committed.</p><p>There are no plans to withdraw capability or cancel equipment programmes.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2015-06-09T15:36:38.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348661/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348661/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348661/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-04","Ministry of Defence: Cost Effectiveness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans he has for (a) withdrawal of capabilities, (b) cancellation of programmes, (c) reduction of personnel and (d) other measures as a result of the £500 million reduction in his Department's budget outlined by the Chancellor of the Exchequer.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","1245"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348662","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-09","<p>Ships' complements are not fixed; they vary, even across a class, depending on equipment fits and tasking. In the longer term, advances in technology for our next generations of ships, submarines and aircraft will involve manning level adjustments while maintaining operational capability.</p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-06-09T15:26:11.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348662/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348662/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348662/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-04","Warships: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans his Department has to reduce the number of crew on Royal Navy warships.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","1132"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348663","Cabinet Office","false","2015-06-09","<p>The National Security Council (NSC) approves the overall strategy and direction of the Conflict Security and Stability Fund (CSSF).</p><p>As the Written Ministerial statement of 12 March set out, the NSC has agreed a range of country and regional strategies, along with approaches on peacekeeping and multilateral institutions which together form a strategic framework for NSC Departments to prioritise HMG’s effort to tackle instability and insecurity overseas.</p><p>The NSC has agreed CSSF allocations for FY15/16. These allocations may change during the course of FY15/16 to reflect changing priorities or to enable the Government to respond more effectively to new cases of conflict and instability.</p><p> </p>","West Dorset","Mr Oliver Letwin",,"2015-06-09T14:59:19.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348663/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Letwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348663/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348663/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-06-04","Conflict, Stability and Security Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how the work of the Conflict, Security and Stability Fund is co-ordinated at ministerial level; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","1139"
