"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348665","Department for Education","false","2015-06-09","<p>Responsibility for coordinating central government funding to Kids Company was transferred from the Department for Education to the Cabinet Office in April 2013. Details of ministerial meetings will be published in the department’s quarterly returns in due course.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2015-06-09T16:48:14.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348665/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348665/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348665/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-06-04","Kids Company: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what discussions she has had with the children's charity Kids Company on the provision of long-term Government funding to that charity.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","1140"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348666","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-09","<p /> <p>The Department does not hold information regarding the number of households who have claimed Discretionary Housing Payments (DHP) in constituency areas. In June last year the Department released a publication detailing Local Authorities use of DHP in 2013/14, which included the number of awards made.</p><p> </p><p>The information can be found here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/discretionary-housing-payments-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/discretionary-housing-payments/statistics</a></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-09T10:53:37.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348666/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348666/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348666/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-04","Housing Benefit: Southwark","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many households in the London Borough of Southwark received Discretionary Housing Payment in  (a) 2012-13, (b) 2013-14 and (c) 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","1143"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348667","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-09","<p /> <p>The Department does not hold information regarding the number of households who have claimed Discretionary Housing Payments (DHP) in constituency areas. In June last year the Department released a publication detailing Local Authorities use of DHP in 2013/14, which included the number of awards made.</p><p> </p><p>The information can be found here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/discretionary-housing-payments-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/discretionary-housing-payments/statistics</a></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-09T10:57:42.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348667/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348667/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348667/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-04","Housing Benefit: Camberwell and Peckham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many households in Camberwell and Peckham constituency received Discretionary Housing Payment in (a) 2012-13, (b) 2013-14 and (c) 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","1144"
