"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348669","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-12","<p>The Government is concerned about the reducing space for civil society and freedom of expression in Azerbaijan, including the detention of a number of high profile members of civil society. The Foreign and Commonwealth Office has issued a number of statements expressing concern, most recently on 17 and 23 April 2015, following the sentencing of human rights defender, Rasul Jafarov, and human rights lawyer, Intigam Aliyev respectively. We consistently raise our concerns both bilaterally and in international organisations such as the Council of Europe, the Organisation for Security and Co-operation in Europe and the UN. We have encouraged Azerbaijan to use the opportunity of hosting the European Games to address legitimate concerns about restrictions on human rights. <br><br>The Parliamentary Under Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my hon. friend the Member for Bournemouth East (Tobias Ellwood) will represent the UK at the Opening Ceremony of the European Games on 12 June.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2015-06-12T11:35:15.04Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348669/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348669/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348669/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-04","Azerbaijan: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the human rights situation in Azerbaijan; and whether the UK will be represented by a minister at the European Games in that country.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","1128"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348670","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-11","<p>UK Trade &amp; Investment (UKTI), the Government Department that helps UK exporters and companies seeking to export, provides details of its main helpline (+44 (0)20 7215 5000) on its publications and its website at <a href="http://www.gov.uk/ukti" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/ukti</a>.</p><p> </p><p>UKTI has an ongoing programme of activities to promote its services to potential and existing exporters. When promoting specific activities e.g. an event, UKTI provides customers with the contact point most relevant to the activity rather than the helpline itself. In line with government strategy of being digital by default UKTI will provide an online enquiry form or a contact email address as the preferred option to contact us and receive our services.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-06-11T11:47:06.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348670/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348670/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348670/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-04","Exports: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps his Department plans to take to promote helpline services for UK exporters and firms seeking to export.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","1156"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348671","Home Office","false","2015-06-09","<p>All public services, including the police, need to take their fair share of the savings to reduce the deficit and help the country live within its means. Final police funding settlement allocations for 2015/16 were confirmed on 10 February, following a debate and vote in the House of Commons. After careful consideration, the Government decided that, as in previous years, all police forces in England and Wales would receive the same percentage reduction in core central Government funding. This is a transparent and straight forward approach and was the basis on which many Police and Crime Commissioners and forces had made their financial plans.</p><p>The Government has committed to a fundamental review of the police funding formula to ensure that allocations to local forces are fair and appropriate. We will consult the police fully in due course.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-06-09T11:55:12.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348671/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348671/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348671/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-06-04","Police: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what factors she took into account when deciding funding reductions for each police force in England and Wales; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","1170"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348672","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-11","<p>Any direct costs will be funded from the Rural Payments Agency.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-06-11T13:05:51.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348672/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348672/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348672/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-04","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, under what budget stream will the additional costs her Department and the Royal Payments Agency have incurred as a result of changes to the process for submitting an application for the Basic Payment Scheme be met.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","1173"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348673","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-12","<p>Ensuring successful delivery of the Basic Payments Scheme in 2015 is our priority and the core of the Rural Payments System is working well. We are also looking carefully at how best to develop the system, including the mapping functionality, in order to support delivery of the Basic Payment Scheme in future years.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","1177","2015-06-12T13:27:00.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348673/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348673/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348673/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-04","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what progress her Department is making in ensuring the mapping functionality of the system for making payments under the Basic Payments Scheme is working; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","1176"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348674","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-12","<p>Ensuring successful delivery of the Basic Payments Scheme in 2015 is our priority and the core of the Rural Payments System is working well. We are also looking carefully at how best to develop the system, including the mapping functionality, in order to support delivery of the Basic Payment Scheme in future years.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","1176","2015-06-12T13:27:00.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348674/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348674/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348674/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-04","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment she has made of the time taken for the mapping functionality of the Rural Payment's Agency computer for Basic Payments Scheme applications to fully work; and what assessment she has made on whether that computer system will need to be completely replaced.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","1177"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348675","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-10","<p>There are many reasons why farmers may choose to use agents or third party suppliers and so we would not look to provide compensation for these business based decisions. We are providing targeted support to make it as easy as possible for both farmers and agents to submit a claim.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-06-10T13:34:48.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348675/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348675/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348675/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-04","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if she will compensate farmers who have already paid agents or third party suppliers to register their Basic Payments Scheme claims online for additional charges incurred by them.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","1178"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348676","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-12","<p>As a result of the complexity of the new 2015 Common Agricultural Policy the European Commission offered all Member States the option to extend the deadline for Basic Payment Scheme applications from 15 May to 15 June. As a result of this derogation Defra will not incur penalties for choosing to extend the application deadline to 15 June.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-06-12T13:33:24.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348676/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348676/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348676/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-04","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what penalties her Department will incur under the CAP regime for late applications for payments under the Basic Payments Scheme.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","1179"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348677","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-11","<p>Exact costs of the change to the new approach for the Basic Payment Scheme 2015 to Defra and Rural Payments Agency are still being assessed.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-06-11T13:45:22.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348677/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348677/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348677/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-04","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what costs (a) her Department and (b) the Royal Payments Agency have incurred through reverting to a paper based system for claiming under the Basic Payments Scheme.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","1180"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348678","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-12","<p>The Rural Payments Agency will be making full payments as early as possible in the payment window. Payments will start from December and the vast majority will be made by the end of January. This is in line with the experience of recent years.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-06-12T13:28:07.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348678/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348678/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348678/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-04","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what advice she has received on whether the one month delay in the Basic Payments Scheme registration deadline for farmers to make their claims under the new CAP will lead to a delay in the paying out of claims.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","1181"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348679","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-10","<p>The Rural Payments Agency incurred an overspend of £0.5m against its Capital DEL in 2014-15. It incurred an underspend of £2.7m against its Resource DEL.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-06-10T13:39:46.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348679/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348679/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348679/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-04","Rural Payments Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what underspends were incurred in (a) Capital DEL and (b) Resource DEL in the Rural Payments Agency at end year 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","1182"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348680","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-09","<p>The Government is considering the responses to the consultation on the route from the West Midlands to Manchester, Leeds and beyond including how to bring the benefits to the North as quickly as possible. It will set out how it plans to take forward HS2 Phase Two later this year.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-06-09T09:36:32.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348680/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348680/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348680/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-04","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of whether (a) delivering the Leeds to Sheffield section of High Speed 2's eastern leg earlier than currently planned would require a separate hybrid bill to be presented to the House and (b) such plans would involve the construction of connections to the East Coast Main Line and the Midland Main Line.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","1208"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348681","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-09","<p>The Rural Payments Agency (RPA) has issued all pre-populated Basic Payments Scheme (BPS) 2015 application forms (BP5) and maps.</p><p>We expect all those farmers who wish to claim BPS to have registered their claims by the deadline of 15 June. We do not anticipate requesting any further extension of the deadline.</p><p>As of 8 June the RPA has received 58,836 completed BPS claims, which is what would be expected at this stage of the claim window. This is good progress as we move towards the deadline.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","1213 ; 1214 ; 1215","2015-06-09T09:23:39.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348681/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348681/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348681/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-04","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what proportion of Basic Payment Scheme applications will be registered by 15 June 2015; and whether she expects to seek a further extension to the deadline for applications.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","1212"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348682","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-09","<p>The Rural Payments Agency (RPA) has issued all pre-populated Basic Payments Scheme (BPS) 2015 application forms (BP5) and maps.</p><p>We expect all those farmers who wish to claim BPS to have registered their claims by the deadline of 15 June. We do not anticipate requesting any further extension of the deadline.</p><p>As of 8 June the RPA has received 58,836 completed BPS claims, which is what would be expected at this stage of the claim window. This is good progress as we move towards the deadline.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","1212 ; 1214 ; 1215","2015-06-09T09:23:40.04Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348682/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348682/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/348682/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-04","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many farmers who wish to claim Basic Payment Scheme payments have yet to receive (a) prepopulated forms and (b) maps for use in the paper-based system.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","1213"
